<Paragraph>
Tree Navigator is used to navigate up / down the Hierarchy-based object. This sample showcases the following functionalities of the tree navigator control.
</Paragraph>
<List>
<ListItem><Paragraph>The visual styles denote  built-in themes, including metro, office themes, visual studio, etc.</Paragraph></ListItem>
<ListItem><Paragraph>Supports two types of navigation mode: </Paragraph>
		<Paragraph>
		- The parent item can be viewed in the default mode with the back button at the top of the tree navigator, and the child items are positioned below the parent object.
		</Paragraph>
		<Paragraph>
		- Both the parent and child item(s) are shown in stack position in extended mode.
		</Paragraph>
</ListItem>

</List>
